A passenger vehicle approached from behind and stopped behind the Waymo AV before eventually proceeding forward and making contact with the rear of the Waymo AV while the AV was still stopped at the red light. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo sustained damage.

A Zoox vehicle in autonomous mode was proceeding straight in its lane on Mason Street in San Francisco, CA when an occupant of a parallel parked car (Vehicle 2) abruptly opened its rear passenger side door into the side of the Zoox vehicle, causing minor damage to both vehicles. The Zoox operator disengaged as a result of the contact. There were no injuries and the police were not called.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle (“Cruise AV”), operating in manual mode, was traveling northbound on 13th Street in the rightmost lane between Folsom Street and South Van Ness Avenue. At the same time, a Model 3 Tesla traveling in the adjacent center lane alongside the Cruise AV attempted to change lanes in front of the Cruise AV over a solid white line into the rightmost lane in which the Cruise AV was traveling. During this maneuver, the Model 3 Tesla made contact with the Cruise AV’s driver side rear wheel and wheel well, and driver side rear passenger door, damaging the Tesla’s front passenger side wheel well . The parties exchanged information and there were no reported injuries.

address/location of accident: Intersection of Folsom Street and 2nd Street
accident decription: A Zoox vehicle in manual mode was stationary at a red right turn arrow northeast on Folsom Street with brake lights and right turn signal illuminated, waiting to make a turn onto souttheast 2nd Street. Vehicle 2, behind the Zoox vehicle, proceeded and made contact with the left rear sensor and bumper of the Zoox vehicle. There were no injuries and police were not called.

Manufacturers Name: Mercedes-Benz Research & Development North America, Inc.
business name: MERCEDES-BENZ RESEARCH & DEVELOPMENT NORTH AMERICA, INC.
accident decription: The subject Mercedes-Benz DRIVE PILOT test vehicle was traveling between 15 – 20 mph in the #2 northbound lane on the 605 Freeway in California in stop and go traffic with the L3 ADS activated by the driver. The vehicle’s ADS determined that a truck traveling in the adjacent lane had a trajectory towards the Drive Pilot’s lane, and so the Mercedes-Benz test vehicle autonomously applied the brakes to avoid a collision.  After applying the brakes and bringing itself to a standstill, the Mercedes-Benz was then struck in the rear bumper by a trailing semi-truck that did not stop in time.  No injuries were reported, no airbags deployed in either vehicle, and both vehicles were able to be driven from the scene of the incident. The Mercedes-Benz vehicle experienced minor damage to the rear bumper, and no damage was observed on the semi-truck at the scene. The CA Traffic Collision Report for the subject incident noted a violation of California Vehicle Code 22350 (unsafe speed for traffic conditions) by the semi-truck in the #2 lane that struck the rear bumper of the Mercedes-Benz.

A Zoox vehicle in autonomous mode was making a right turn to travel southwest onto 2nd Street from Folsom Street from lane 1 when Vehicle 2 crossed from lane 3 into the Zoox vehicle's lane and made contact with the Zoox vehicle's front sensors before making the right turn.  Vehicle 2 did not stop before leaving the scene. No information was exchanged. There were no injuries and the police were not called.

address/location of accident: Embarcadero between Howard St. and Folsom St.
accident decription: A Zoox vehicle in autonomy was stopped with brake lights illuminated in traffic southbound on Embarcadero Street towards Folsom Street. When traffic ahead began to move the Zoox vehicle was appropriately following the car ahead at low speed when it was rear ended by Vehicle #2 at low speed. The other party did not stop to exchange information and left the scene. There were no injuries and police were not called.

Manufacturers Name: Mercedes-Benz Research & Development North America, Inc.
business name: MERCEDES-BENZ RESEARCH & DEVELOPMENT NORTH AMERICA, INC.
accident decription: The subject Mercedes-Benz vehicle was driving in stop and go traffic on the 405 south freeway in Gardena, California with the L3 ADS activated. The test route selected by the driver in the vehicle's navigation system indicated an upcoming exit, so the driver began to prepare for a lane change towards the highway exit by deactivating the L3 ADS and activating the turn signal. Once the vehicle was in conventional driving mode, the driver looked for a gap in the adjacent lane to merge towards the exit lane, applied the brakes, and slowed the vehicle down. The SUV following the Mercedes-Benz vehicle did not respond in time to the vehicle's braking and contacted the rear of the Mercedes-Benz approximately 10 seconds after the L3 ADS was deactivated.  The Mercedes-Benz vehicle experienced minor damage to the rear bumper. No injuries were reported, no airbags deployed in either vehicle, and both vehicles were driven from the scene of the incident.

A Zoox vehicle in autonomous mode was slowing to a stop with brake lights illuminated behind traffic on northbound 5th Street near Jesse Street when a vehicle behind made contact at approximately 10mph. There were no injuries and police were not called.

address/location of accident: North Point Street at Buchanan Street
accident decription: On February 15, 2023 at 5:43 AM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving road debris on North Point Street at Buchanan Street.The Waymo AV was proceeding East on North Point Street through the intersection with Buchanan Street when the front of the Waymo AV made contact with cardboard debris. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage.

On February 21st, a test vehicle operating in manual driving mode was making a u-turn from Westbound to Eastbound Homestead Road at the intersection with Kennewick Drive in Sunnyvale when the right front tire and rim made contact with the curb.  No injuries were reported and law enforcement was not called to the scene.  The test vehicle sustained damage to the right front rim.

address/location of accident: Harrison St. and Sixth St. Intersection
accident decription: A Zoox vehicle in manual mode was proceeding southbound in the turn lane on Sixth Street with a green light, yielding to a pedestrian before completing a right turn onto eastbound Harrison Street, in San Francisco, CA with turn signals illuminated. A large truck in the left adjacent lane abruptly turned right and cut in front of the Zoox vehicle making contact with the left front sensor. There were no injuries, the other vehicle did not stop to exchange information, and police were not called.

On February 24, 2023 at 12:15 AM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger vehicle on Toland Street at Hudson Avenue.The Waymo AV was traveling southwest on Toland Street in autonomous mode. While the Waymo AV was making a left turn onto Hudson Avenue, a passenger vehicle proceeded into the intersection from the left and made contact with the left side of the Waymo AV. The other vehicle immediately left the scene. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. Both vehicles sustained damage.

On February 25th, 2023 at 7:23 AM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a heavy truck on 25th Street at Noe Street. The Waymo AV was proceeding East on 25th Street near the intersection with Noe Street when it came to a stop to yield to a heavy truck traveling West on 25th Street. As the heavy truck moved past the Waymo AV, the front left tire of the heavy truck made contact with the rear left sensor of the Waymo AV. The heavy truck then left the scene. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage.

On February 25th, 2023 at 9:45 AM/PM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a heavy truck on Pacific Avenue at Sansome Street.The Waymo AV was making a right turn to travel west on Pacific Avenue. As the Waymo AV turned, the rear right tire of the Waymo AV made contact with the lowered loading lift of a heavy truck parked partially across the parking lot entrance. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was not engaged and a test driver was operating the Waymo AV in manual mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage.

On March 1, 2023 at 8:27 PM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco was in a collision involving a fixed object on O’Farrell Street near Anzavista Avenue.As the Waymo AV was leaving a parking lot to turn left onto O’Farrell Street, the front of the Waymo AV made contact with a chain that was connected between a parking lot road sign and a temporary pole. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The road sign fell down due to tension on the chain.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("Cruise AV"), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling eastbound on Bryant Street in the rightmost lane between 11th Street and 10th Street. As the Cruise AV proceeded straight into the intersection with 10th Street, a semi-trailer truck traveling in the lane to the left of the Cruise AV began to make a right turn onto 10th Street and crossed into the Cruise AV’s lane without a turn signal. The Cruise AV braked and the semi-trailer truck made contact with the left side of the Cruise AV, causing damage to the driver side front, rear, and bumper of the Cruise AV. The parties exchanged information and there were no injuries.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("Cruise AV"), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was at a complete stop in response to a red light on northbound Polk Street at the intersection with Sutter Street. The Cruise AV began to proceed as the light turned green when an Infiniti Q50 passed the Cruise AV in the oncoming traffic lane and began performing “donuts” in the intersection. The Cruise AV began to initiate a left turn onto Sutter Street when the Infiniti Q50 made contact with the Cruise AV’s front driver side bumper, causing damage to the front driver side bumper, front driver side fascia and front driver side headlight. The driver of the Infiniti Q50 left the scene without exchanging information. There were no reported injuries and the Cruise AV was towed from the incident.

Our Autonomous vehicle (car 1) was in conventional mode stopped at the traffic light on Embarcadero and Washington. A black color Dodge Challenger (car 2) attempted to bypass our car (car 1) from the rear and in doing so hit our car (car 1) right side rear bumper. At the time of collision our AV (Car 1) was stopped traveling 0 mph and the Dodge Challenger (car 2) was traveling less than 5 mph.  The damage is minor and left a small scratch. After exchanging information both parties agreed to leave the scene

address/location of accident: Cesar Chavez Street at Mission Street
accident decription: On March 12, 2023 at 9:28 PM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on Cesar Chavez Street at Mission Street.The Waymo AV was stopped in the dedicated left turn lane facing west on Cesar Chavez Street, awaiting a green signal to turn onto Mission Street. The signal for traffic proceeding west on Cesar Chavez Street turned green, and traffic in adjacent lanes began moving. The left turn arrow signal for the dedicated turn lane occupied by the Waymo AV remained red. The passenger car that had been stopped directly behind the Waymo AV began moving forward. The front of the passenger car made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV.At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The passenger car sustained minor damage.

On March 16, 2023 at 2:19 AM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Bruno, CA was in a collision involving road debris on Interstate 280 at the interchange ramp for Interstate 380 (Exit 43A). The Waymo AV was traveling south on Interstate 280 in the rightmost exit lane for Exit 43A towards Interstate 380 when it made contact with road debris (tire scrap). At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was (engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo AV sustained damage.

On March 16, 2023 at 5:10 PM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on Bayshore Boulevard between Flower Street and Cortland Avenue. The Waymo AV was traveling north on Bayshore Boulevard in autonomous mode, merging into the rightmost lane.  As the Waymo AV merged, the test driver transitioned from autonomous mode to manual mode and began accelerating. The front of the Waymo AV made contact with the rear of a passenger car that was stopped in the rightmost lane. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was not engaged and a test driver was operating the Waymo AV in manual mode. Both the Waymo AV and the passenger car sustained damage.

A Zoox vehicle in manual mode northwest on Division St. in San Francisco, CA scraped a parked car at low speed as it was pulling into a driveway, making contact with its left front bumper. There were no injuries and police were not called.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("Cruise AV"), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling southbound on 25th Avenue between Clement Street and Geary Boulevard. The Cruise AV entered the intersection with Geary Boulevard on a green light. As the Cruise AV was passing through the intersection, a Mercedes Sedan traveling eastbound on Geary Boulevard entered the intersection on a red light and shortly thereafter made contact with the Cruise AV, damaging the front right quarter of the Cruise AV. The Mercedes Sedan then made contact with a nearby building, resulting in damage to the property. Police and Emergency Medical Services were called to the scene. The Cruise AV was towed from the scene. Occupants of the Mercedes Sedan received medical treatment at the scene and were not transported by Emergency Medical Services.

On March 20, 2023 at 10:43 AM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in Los Angeles, California was in a collision involving an SUV on Venice Boulevard at La Cienega.The Waymo AV was stopped in the center lane of a three-lane road behind a passenger vehicle for a red light facing southwest on Venice Boulevard at La Cienega in autonomous mode. The light turned green while cross-traffic remained backed up in the intersection. The Waymo AV nudged forward and slowed to a stop, yielding for the blocking cross traffic. A passenger vehicle that had been stopped behind the Waymo AV proceeded forward and made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo AV sustained damage.

On March 20, 2023 at approximately 8:04 PM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a pothole on Bayshore Boulevard near Jerrold Avenue. The Waymo AV was traveling in the second lane on a four-lane section of northbound Bayshore Boulevard when the passenger side rear tire made contact with a pothole. The tire began to deflate and the Waymo AV pulled over on a side street. At the time of impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("Cruise AV"), operating in manual mode, was traveling westbound in the leftmost lane on Sacramento Street between Larkin Street and Polk Street. As the Cruise AV operator attempted to parallel park behind a Hyundai Tucson, the Cruise AV made contact with the Hyundai Tucson. The parties exchanged information. There were no damages to the Cruise AV and there were no reported injuries.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("Cruise AV"), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling eastbound on Clay Street between Hyde Street and Leavenworth Street. Shortly before the intersection with Leavenworth Street, the Cruise AV made contact with a downed power cable on Clay Street and came to a stop. This caused damage to the Cruise AV’s front driver side radar assembly. There were no injuries.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("Cruise AV"), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling southbound on Polk Street near the intersection with Clay Street. Shortly after passing through the intersection with Clay Street, the Cruise AV made contact with a downed power cable stretching across Polk Street and came to a stop. This caused damage to the Cruise AV’s front fascia. There were no injuries. Cruise was informed by law enforcement to keep the Cruise AV stationary until the power cables were cleared. During the time that the power cable was being cleared and that the Cruise AV was stopped, the Cruise AV ran low on battery power and did not have enough power to return to Cruise facilities on its own. The Cruise AV was therefore towed from the scene once the power cables were cleared.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle (“Cruise AV”), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling southbound on Shafter Avenue between Ingalls Street and Hawes Street. Shortly after the intersection with Ingalls Street, the Cruise AV made contact with a tow dolly attached to the back of a double-parked truck, damaging the front passenger side bumper and front passenger side fender of the Cruise AV. There were no reported injuries.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle (“Cruise AV”), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling westbound on Turk Boulevard between Roselyn Terrace and Kittredge Terrace. The Cruise AV came to a complete stop for a vehicle in the process of letting passengers out that was stopped in the Cruise AV’s lane of travel. A Smart Car traveling behind the Cruise AV came to a complete stop behind the Cruise AV. A Honda Accord trailing behind the Smart Car began to decelerate but made contact with the Smart Car, pushing the Smart Car forward into the Cruise AV’s rear bumper. The parties exchanged information. There were no damages to the Cruise AV and there were no reported injuries.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("Cruise AV"), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling on westbound Haight Street between Ashbury Street and Masonic Avenue.  At the same time, a San Francisco Municipal Railway (“MUNI”) Bus stopped ahead of the Cruise AV. Shortly thereafter, the Cruise AV made contact with the rear bumper of the MUNI Bus, damaging the front fascia and front fender of the Cruise AV. The parties exchanged information. There were no reported injuries and the Cruise AV was towed from the scene.

address/location of accident: Jack London Alley at Varney Place
accident decription: On April 3, 2023 at 10:56 PM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving an SUV on Jack London Alley at Varney Place.While traveling northwest on Jack London Alley, the Waymo AV came to a stop to yield to an oncoming SUV in a narrow passageway. The SUV proceeded around the Waymo AV and made contact with the left rear sensor housing of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The driver of the SUV stopped briefly but left before sharing their information. The Waymo sustained damage.

On April 5, 2023 at 10:46 AM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on Potrero Avenue at 21st Street.The Waymo AV was traveling southbound on Potrero Avenue in the leftmost lane as it was approaching the intersection with 21st Street. The signal for traffic proceeding south on Potrero Avenue was green for the Waymo AV as it approached the intersection. As the Waymo AV approached, an individual riding a motorized scooter traveling north on Potrero Avenue proceeded to turn left onto westbound 21st Street, across the paths of the Waymo AV and other oncoming vehicles. The Waymo AV began to brake, and the Waymo AV test driver transitioned to manual mode and brought the Waymo AV to a stop. A passenger car traveling directly behind the Waymo AV then made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. The individual riding the scooter was not contacted by the Waymo AV or any other vehicle. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was not engaged and a test driver was operating the Waymo AV in manual mode. Both the Waymo AV and the passenger car sustained damage, and the individual on the motorized scooter left the scene.

On April 6, 2023 at 10:48 AM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a heavy truck on Randall Street near Harper Street. The Waymo AV was proceeding northwest on Randall Street near the intersection with Harper Street when it came to a stop to yield to a heavy truck traveling southeast on Randall Street. As the heavy truck drove past the Waymo AV, the driver’s side section of the heavy truck made contact with the rear driver’s side sensor of the Waymo AV. The heavy truck then left the scene. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle (“Cruise AV”), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling southbound on 25th Avenue between Clement Street and Geary Boulevard. The Cruise AV entered the intersection with Geary Boulevard on a green light. As the Cruise AV was passing through the intersection, a black Volkswagen Hatchback traveling westbound on Geary Boulevard entered the intersection on a red light and shortly thereafter made contact with the Cruise AV, damaging the driver side doors of the Cruise AV. The driver of the Volkswagen Hatchback left the scene without exchanging information. Police were called to the scene. There were no reported injuries and the Cruise AV was towed from the scene.

address/location of accident: Kearny Street and Commercial Street Intersection
accident decription: A Zoox vehicle in autonomy was proceeding northbound on Kearny Street in stop-and-go traffic through an active construction zone. At the same time, an e-scooter traveling near the right curb was passing other slow traffic behind the Zoox vehicle. Before the e-scooter could also pass the Zoox vehicle on the right, the e-scooter weaved away from the curb, seemingly to avoid a drainage grate, and came within a close following distance behind the Zoox vehicle. As the Zoox vehicle came to a stop again for traffic ahead the e-scooter rider did not stop, and the e-scooter made contact with the right rear tail light of the Zoox vehicle. The e-scooter rider remained upright, did not stop to exchange information, and immediately rode off while the Zoox vehicle was still stopped. There were no injuries and police were not called. The damage to the Zoox vehicle was limited to a cracked tail light lens.

A Zoox vehicle in manual mode was traveling eastbound on Lombard St. towards Leavenworth St. following a sharp curve in the road when it made contact with a concrete abutment on the right. There were no injuries and police were not called. Autonomy was not engaged at any point during the drive cycle proceeding the event.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle (“Cruise AV”), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling westbound on Turk Street Street between Webster Street and Laguna Street. The Cruise AV came to a complete stop for a double-parked Sedan in the leftmost lane. The Cruise AV began to maneuver around and to the right of the Sedan when the Sedan reversed into the Cruise AV, damaging the Cruise AV’s front driver side bumper. The driver of the Sedan left the scene without exchanging information. There were no reported injuries.

On April 12, 2023 at 5:29 PM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in Santa Monica, California was in a collision involving an SUV on Wilshire Boulevard at 26th Street. The Waymo AV was traveling southwest on Wilshire Boulevard in the rightmost lane as it was approaching the intersection with 26th Street. The signal for traffic proceeding southwest on Wilshire Boulevard was red as the Waymo AV approached the intersection and came to a stop. The signal for traffic proceeding southwest on Wilshire Boulevard then turned green, and traffic in adjacent lanes began moving while the Waymo AV waited for traffic in its lane to begin to move.The SUV that had been stopped directly behind the Waymo AV began moving forward and the front of the SUV made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo sustained damage.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("Cruise AV"), operating in manual mode, was at a complete stop in response to a red light in the rightmost lane on westbound Geary Boulevard at the intersection with Larkin Street. While the Cruise AV was fully stopped, a Mercedes SUV exited a parking lot onto westbound Geary Boulevard, pulled behind and to the left of the Cruise AV, and made contact with the left side of the Cruise AV, causing damage to the Cruise AV’s rear driver side door and rear driver side wheel well. The parties exchanged information. The Cruise AV operator in the Cruise AV later reported head, shoulder and back injuries.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("Cruise AV"), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was at a complete stop in response to a red light on 10th Street at the intersection with Division Street. The Cruise AV began to make a right turn onto Division Street after the light turned green  before yielding to a pedestrian in the crosswalk. Shortly thereafter, a silver Infiniti Sedan traveling behind the Cruise AV made contact with the Cruise AV’s rear bumper, causing damage to the Cruise AV’s rear fascia. The driver of the Infiniti Sedan left the scene without exchanging information. There were no reported injuries.

Manufacturers Name: Mercedes-Benz Research & Development North America, Inc.
business name: MERCEDES-BENZ RESEARCH & DEVELOPMENT NORTH AMERICA, INC.
accident decription: The Mercedes-Benz was leaving the off-ramp of EB Central Expressway and approached the merge at NB San Thomas Expressway. The driver yielded to cross traffic at the merge when the Porsche Cayenne vehicle rear-ended the Mercedes-Benz.

The Waymo AV was traveling east on 25th Street between Sanchez Street and Vicksburg Street when it approached an SUV that was stopped in the lane in front of the Waymo AV. The Waymo AV began passing the stopped SUV on the left when the SUV began reversing in the lane. The Waymo AV then stopped behind and to the left of the SUV, and the SUV continued reversing and began a turning maneuver to enter a parking space. The left side of the SUV made contact with the front right corner of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV was stopped and the AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. Both vehicles sustained damage.

On April 30, 2023 at 1:53 PM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving an SUV on Oak Street at Octavia Boulevard. While the Waymo AV was parked at the right side curb of the road on Oak Street, an SUV that was passing the parked Waymo AV in the rightmost lane made contact with the rear driver’s side of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV did not sustain damage, while the SUV sustained damage.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("Cruise AV"), operating in supervised autonomous mode, was at a complete stop in response to a red light on 36th Avenue at the intersection with Lincoln Way. The Cruise AV began to make a left turn onto Lincoln Way after the light turned green. While the Cruise AV was in the intersection completing the turn, the Cruise AV operator disengaged from autonomous into manual mode. After the disengagement, the Cruise AV operator continued straight forward, and shortly thereafter, made contact with the right curb and concrete guardrail on Lincoln Way. This caused damage to the Cruise AV’s front passenger side bumper and front passenger side fascia. The Cruise AV operator reported injuries and the Cruise AV was towed from the incident.

On Monday May 1st at 11:41am a Weride autonomous vehicle (Vehicle 1) was in Autonomous Mode stopped at the intersection of Bay St towards Columbus Ave appropriately yielding to a illegally U turning skateboard on Bay St North to South direction in front of the AV (Vehicle 1). While yielding, a bicyclist was coming from behind our AV (Vehicle 1) head was turned left possibly looking for cross traffic. When the cyclist turned his head forward, it was too late to react in time to our stopped vehicle(Vehicle 1) with the given distance and speed they were traveling at in which the cyclist collided with our vehicle (Vehicle 1). Our Weride safety officer immediately disengaged and hand signaled to the bicyclist to pull over to the closest safe place to park as to not obstruct traffic. As our safety officer parked and got out of the car to check on the bicyclist, the bicyclist was already on in motion on his bicycle and "fist bumped" our safety officer while passing by him and leaving the scene without exchanging any information.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("Cruise AV"), operating in manual mode, was departing from the Three Embarcadero Center garage facility. As the Cruise AV was leaving the garage, the garage gate began to lower and made contact with the Cruise AV, damaging the roof Lidar assembly. There were no reported injuries.

On May 3, 2023 at 10:32 AM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving an SUV on Pine Street near Broderick Street.The Waymo AV was traveling in autonomous mode in the middle lane on westbound Pine Street between Divisadero Street and Broderick Street. A slower traveling van in the left adjacent lane began to initiate a right lane change in front of the Waymo AV, and the Waymo AV test driver transitioned to manual mode and braked. The SUV traveling behind the Waymo AV then made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was not engaged and a test driver was operating the Waymo AV in manual mode. The Waymo AV and SUV sustained damage.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("Cruise AV"), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling northbound on Franklin Street between Clay Street and Sacramento Street. As the Cruise AV passed through the intersection with Sacramento Street, a scooterist approaching from the rear merged into the Cruise AV's lane behind the Cruise AV. The Cruise AV began to brake, and the scooterist made contact with the rear window and rear bumper of the Cruise AV. This caused damage to the rear window, rear bumper and driver side rear headlight of the Cruise AV. The parties exchanged information. There were no injuries reported at the scene and police were not called. The scooterist later reported injuries.

On May 6, 2023 at 8:48 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger vehicle on Post Street at Webster Street.While traveling west on Post Street, the Waymo AV was executing a pullover maneuver in autonomous mode and made contact with the left rear bumper of a parked vehicle. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. Both vehicles sustained damage.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle (“Cruise AV”), operating in manual mode, was traveling northbound on Polk Street between Pine Street and California Street. As the Cruise AV was passing through the intersection with California Street on a green light, a stand-up scooterist traveling eastbound on California Street entered the intersection on a red light and shortly thereafter made contact with the Cruise AV, damaging the Cruise AV’s front and rear driver side doors, front driver side radar assembly and rear driver side door handle. The scooterist left the scene without exchanging information. There were no reported injuries.

On May 7, 2023 at 3:27 PM PDT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a cyclist on Bay Street near Mason Street. The Waymo AV was traveling westbound in the left lane on Bay Street and had just passed Mason Street when it detected an oncoming pickup truck traveling eastbound in the Waymo AV’s lane. The Waymo AV stopped and the pickup truck re-entered the correct lane for eastbound traffic and passed the Waymo AV. The pickup truck was immediately followed by a large group of cyclists traveling eastbound in multiple lanes of the roadway, including the right lanes and on the wrong side of the double-yellow centerline. The Waymo AV remained stopped as the oncoming cyclists rode around both sides of the Waymo AV. One cyclist then made contact with the front of the stationary Waymo AV, and then immediately left the scene. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage.

address/location of accident: Our Lady's Way & Great America Pkwy
accident decription: On May 11th, a test vehicle operating in manual driving mode was traveling Eastbound on Our Lady’s Way in Santa Clara and stopped in traffic behind a stop sign at the intersection with Great America Parkway.  A Volkswagen Jetta failed to stop and struck the rear of the test vehicle.  No injuries were reported and law enforcement was not called to the scene.  Both vehicles sustained minor damage.

A Zoox vehicle in autonomous mode was traveling north on Harrison St. The Zoox vehicle began coming to a gradual stop for traffic ahead when it was rear ended by vehicle 2 at low speed. There was minor damage and police were not called. The Zoox operator reported a "sore neck and back."

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("Cruise AV"), operating in manual mode, was parked in a parking space in a Costco garage facility. As the Cruise AV operator was reversing out of the parking space, the Cruise AV made contact with a cement pillar, damaging the front driver side radar assembly of the Cruise AV. There were no reported injuries.

A Zoox vehicle in manual mode was stopped northbound at the intersection of Montgomery St and Broadway at a red traffic light when another vehicle making a left turn from westbound Broadway onto southbound Montgomery St erratically veered toward the Zoox vehicle, resulting in a low speed collision with our front bumper. The driver initially stopped and partially opened the drivers door, but then drove away from the scene. Police were not called and no injuries were reported.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle (“Cruise AV”), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling eastbound on Folsom Street between 8th Street and Langton Street. As the Cruise AV approached the intersection with Langton Street, the Cruise AV traveled over a pothole, which blew out the front driver side tire and caused the Cruise AV to veer into the adjacent parking lane. Shortly thereafter, the Cruise AV made contact with a parked Subaru Impreza, causing damage to the Cruise AV’s front passenger side quarter panel, front passenger side fascia, front driver side tire and rear passenger side quarter panel. Police and Emergency Medical Services were called and the Cruise AV was towed from the scene. The passenger of the Cruise AV was assessed by medical personnel at the scene but was not transported by Emergency Medical Services.

On May 21, 2023 at 10:56 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a small dog on Toland Street at Toland Place.The Waymo AV was traveling southwest on Toland Street when a small dog ran into the street in front of the Waymo AV. The Waymo AV then made contact with the dog, which did not survive. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo AV sustained damage.

Manufacturers Name: Mercedes-Benz Research & Development North America, Inc.
business name: MERCEDES-BENZ RESEARCH & DEVELOPMENT NORTH AMERICA, INC.
accident decription: The Mercedes-Benz was traveling eastbound on Condensa Street at the merge of the eastbound Central Expressway.  The driver of the Mercedes-Benz was yielding to cross-traffic and came to a complete stop as he waited for an opening to merge. The driver of the Mazda following the Mercedes-Benz did not come to a stop and contacted the Mercedes-Benz at the rear bumper. The Mazda was travel <5mph at the time of contact with the Mercedes-Benz. No injuries were incurred and both parties were able to drive away from the incident.

Manufacturers Name: Mercedes-Benz Research & Development North America, Inc.
business name: MERCEDES-BENZ RESEARCH & DEVELOPMENT NORTH AMERICA, INC.
accident decription: THE DRIVER WAS OPERATING THIS VEHICLE ON US HWY 710N IN L2 MODE APPROACHING THE INTERCHANGE WITH THE US HWY 91. AS DRIVER APPROACHED AN OVERPASS, A 4-FOOT LONG STEEL ROD FELL FROM THE BRIDGE AND BOUNCED OFF THE HIGHWAY BEFORE HITTING THE FRONT BUMPER OF THE VEHICLE. THE DRIVER TOOK MANUAL CONTROL AND BROUGHT THE VEHICLE TO A STOP ON THE SHOULDER.  DAMAGE WAS INCURRED TO THE FRONT BUMPER INCLUDING DESTRUCTION OF A CAMERA SENSOR, LIDAR, AND RADAR.  NO INJURIES WERE REPORTED BY THE DRIVER AND HE WAS ABLE TO DRIVE FROM THE SCENE OF THE INCIDENT.

On June 5, 2023, while in supervised (“Drivered”) autonomous mode, a Pony.ai AV was rear-ended twice by a passenger vehicle at the intersection of Warren Ave and Kato Road in Fremont, CA. The Pony.ai AV was stopped at a red stop light when the passenger vehicle directly behind the Pony.ai AV proceeded to rear-end the Pony.ai AV two times in quick succession. The Pony.ai safety operator disengaged the Pony.ai AV from autonomous mode, and,  concerned for his own safety, immediately drove the vehicle back to the Pony.ai Fremont office (a distance of approximately 1 mile). The passenger vehicle which had rear-ended the Pony.ai AV followed  the Pony.ai AV back to Pony.ai’s Fremont office. After a brief interaction during which the driver of the passenger vehicle threatened Pony.ai employees, the passenger vehicle and driver drove away. The Fremont police took a report about the incident. There were no injuries reported.

On June 5, 2023 at 12:53 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a van in a parking lot at 3911 3rd Street.The Waymo AV came to a stop while yielding to a pickup truck which was reversing into a perpendicular parking space in front of the Waymo AV. While the Waymo AV was stopped, a van which was in a parking space immediately to the right of the Waymo AV began reversing out of the parking space. The rear of the van made contact with the right side of the Waymo AV. The Waymo AV sustained damage. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle (“Cruise AV”), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling southbound on Revere Avenue between Industrial Street and Selby Street. The Cruise AV came to a stop behind a GMC Yukon that was stopped diagonally in the Cruise AV’s lane of travel. After the Cruise AV came to a complete stop, the GMC Yukon began reversing further into the Cruise AV’s lane and made contact with the Cruise AV, damaging the front bumper fascia of the Cruise AV. The parties exchanged information and there were no reported injuries.

address/location of accident: E Trimble Rd between Junction Ave and Zanker Rd
accident decription: At 2:06pm a WeRide driverless vehicle (car 1) was stopped behind a big rig truck (vehicle 2). As our vehicle (car 1) was stopped behind the big rig truck, the big rig truck proceeded to reverse backwards and eventually collided into the WeRide vehicle (car 1). Both parties pulled over both involved vehicles and cooperated to exchange information. The damage sustained to the WeRide vehicle was moderate and the big rig truck did not have any damage.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle (“Cruise AV”), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling northbound on Harrison St. between 18th Street and 19th Street. As the Cruise AV was coming to a stop for a stop sign at the intersection with 18th Street, a van approaching from the rear failed to stop behind the Cruise AV and made contact with the Cruise AV's rear bumper, damaging the rear bumper of the Cruise AV. Police and Emergency Medical Services were called and the Cruise AV was towed from the scene. The driver of the van was transported by Emergency Medical Services for further evaluation.

On June 9, 2023 at 2:47 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on Fell Street at Laguna Street.The Waymo AV was maneuvering out of a parallel parking spot at the right side curb on Fell Street. As it reversed, the rear of the Waymo AV made contact with the front of the passenger car parked directly behind it. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was not engaged and a test driver was operating the Waymo AV in manual mode. Both the Waymo AV and the passenger car sustained damage.

On June 11, 2023 at 3:44 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on Santiago Street near 42nd Avenue.The Waymo AV was parallel parked along the curb on eastbound Santiago Street when a passenger car pulled up behind the Waymo AV. The front of the passenger car made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("Cruise AV"), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling eastbound on Sacramento Street between Lyon Street and Baker Street. The Cruise AV approached a motorized articulating boom lift (“ABL”), which was stopped in the Cruise AV’s lane of travel. As the Cruise AV began to maneuver around and to the left of the ABL, the Cruise AV made contact with the arm of the ABL, which was elevated above the roadway. This caused damage to the Cruise AV’s roof Lidar assembly. There were no reported injuries.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("Cruise AV"), operating in manual mode, was parked in a parking space in a Costco lot facility. As the Cruise AV operator was reversing out of the parking space, the Cruise AV made contact with a cement pillar, damaging the front driver side bumper fascia of the Cruise AV. There were no reported injuries.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("Cruise AV"), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling westbound on 19th Street between Capp Street and Mission Street. The Cruise AV slowed to a stop due to a pedestrian on a scooter who entered the lane of traffic in front of the AV and started proceeding in circles. Shortly thereafter, the pedestrian approached the stopped Cruise AV, placed the scooter on the ground in front of the Cruise AV’s front passenger side tire, and walked away off the roadway. After the pedestrian left, the Cruise AV attempted to proceed forward and made contact with the abandoned scooter. There were no damages to the Cruise AV and there were no reported injuries.

On June 18, 2023 at 5:06 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger vehicle on Market Street and Diamond Street.The Waymo AV was stopped for a red light on Market Street at Diamond Street with its turn signal activated to indicate intent to turn left onto Diamond Street. The traffic light turned green, and the Waymo AV slowly moved forward, yielding to oncoming traffic, when the vehicle that had been previously stopped behind the Waymo AV proceeded forward, making contact with the rear bumper of the Waymo AV. The other party immediately left the scene of the event. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. Both vehicles sustained damage.

A Zoox vehicle in manual mode was stopped in stop-and-go traffic southbound on Montgomery St. at the intersection of Pine St. when it was struck from behind by vehicle 2.  Police were not called, and Zoox operators later reported injuries.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle (“Cruise AV”), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling southbound on Tennessee Street between Mariposa Street and 18th Street when it approached a Lexus Sedan that was stopped in the middle of the road between the Cruise AV’s lane of travel and opposite lane of travel. As the Cruise AV passed the stopped Lexus Sedan on the right, the passenger of the Lexus Sedan opened their front passenger side door, making contact with the Cruise AV’s lower front driver side bumper fascia. This caused damage to the Cruise AV’s lower front driver side bumper fascia and front driver side wheel opening molding. The driver of the Lexus Sedan left the scene without exchanging information. There were no reported injuries.

On June 28, 2023 at 9:19 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a pickup truck on Great Highway near Kirkham Street. The Waymo AV was parallel parked along the curb on southbound Great Highway when a pickup truck that was initially parked directly behind the Waymo AV began to maneuver out of its parking spot. As the pickup truck pulled out of the parking spot, it initiated a multi-turn maneuver and reversed into the parked Waymo AV. The rear passenger's side corner of the pickup truck made contact with the driver side rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage.

On June 29, 2023 at 3:39 PM PDT, an Apollo Autonomous Vehicle (“Apollo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California, was in a collision involving a scooter on Moraga Street near 34th Ave. The Apollo AV was traveling westbound on Moraga Street passing the intersection with 34th Ave. The intersection has stop signs clearly installed at all four ways, which require vehicles to make full stop before entering the intersection. The Apollo AV made a full stop, entered and passed approximately 75% of the intersection. A person on scooter coming southbound from 34th Ave.,  approached the intersection. The person on scooter entered the intersection without stopping, then made contact with the passenger rear-side of Apollo AV. Our Apollo AV operator immediately disengaged the AV, pulled over to the closest safe place to park, got out of the car to check the person on scooter, who already left the scene on his scooter without exchanging any information. The Apollo AV had small minor paint scratch, which do not need repair. The police were not called.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle (“Cruise AV”), operating in supervised autonomous mode, was traveling southbound on Selby Street between Palou Avenue and Oakdale Avenue. The Cruise AV came to a stop behind a semi-trailer truck that was slowly reversing diagonally onto Selby Street from the intersection with Palou Avenue. As the semi-trailer truck began encroaching into the Cruise AV’s lane of travel, the Cruise AV operator disengaged from autonomous into manual mode and began reversing the Cruise AV, causing the Cruise AV to back into a different semi-trailer truck parked behind the Cruise AV. This caused damage to the Cruise AV’s rear passenger side wheel molding. The Cruise AV operator left information for the other party and there were no reported injuries.

On June 29, 2023 at 7:50 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, CA was in a collision involving a pickup truck on Jersey Street at Church Street. The Waymo AV was traveling eastbound on Jersey Street and stopped at a stop sign at the intersection of Church Street. While yielding to pedestrians crossing the street, a pickup truck traveling directly behind the Waymo AV made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage.

On June 29, 2023 at 11:18 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in Los Angeles, California was in a collision involving a pick-up truck on 4th Street at S. June Street.The Waymo AV was traveling eastbound on 4th Street and stopped at a stop sign at the intersection of S. June Street when a pick-up truck approached the Waymo AV from behind and made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. The Waymo AV test driver took manual control of the Waymo AV to pull over, and the pick-up truck made further contact the Waymo AV. At the time of the initial impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo AV sustained damage.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle (“Cruise AV”), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling northbound on Franklin Street in the second rightmost lane between Hayes Street and Fell Street. At the same time, a white Kia Forte traveling in the adjacent center lane veered into the Cruise AV’s lane without a turn signal. Shortly thereafter, contact was made with the Cruise AV’s driver side front and rear passenger door, damaging the driver side front and rear passenger door of the Cruise AV. The driver of the white Kia Forte left the scene without exchanging information. There were no reported injuries.

On July 3, 2023 at 1:13 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on Hampshire Street at 21st Street. The Waymo AV was traveling southbound on Hampshire Street in autonomous mode when it began to brake as it approached a stopped van on the oncoming side of the narrow roadway. The Waymo AV test driver transitioned to manual mode and began proceeding straight when the passenger side front sensor housing of the Waymo AV made contact with the driver side mirror of a passenger car parked along the curb on southbound Hampshire Street. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was not engaged and a test driver was operating the Waymo AV in manual mode. Both the Waymo AV and the passenger car sustained damage.

On July 8, 2023 at 3:08 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in Los Angeles, California was in a collision involving a cyclist on S. Alameda Street at 6th Street.The Waymo AV was traveling southbound on S. Alameda Street and preparing to make a right turn onto westbound 6th Street. As the Waymo AV was yielding to cross-traffic and preparing to make a right turn, a cyclist was traveling eastbound on 6th Street and heading the wrong way in the bike lane. The cyclist then turned left, northbound, onto S. Alameda Street, continuing to travel the wrong direction in the bike lane. As the Waymo AV slowly proceeded forward, the cyclist passed the Waymo AV and made contact with the rear passenger side sensor of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo AV sustained damage and the cyclist did not stop, leaving the scene without exchanging information.

On July 11, 2023 at 10:13 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger vehicle on Martin Avenue at Mullen Avenue.While completing a right turn from Martin Avenue onto Mullen Avenue in autonomous mode, the Waymo AV slowed to a stop while entering a narrow roadway. As the Waymo AV started to slowly proceed forward, the test driver transitioned the vehicle to manual mode and proceeded forward, making contact with a parked passenger vehicle. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was not engaged and a test driver was operating the Waymo AV in manual mode. Both vehicles sustained damage.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("Cruise AV"), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling eastbound on McAllister Street between Van Ness Avenue and Polk Street. As the Cruise AV was slowing for a red light at the intersection with Polk Street, an Infiniti Q60 traveling westbound on McAllister Street failed to stop for the red light, entered the intersection, and made contact with a black sedan traveling southbound on Polk Street that entered the intersection on a green light. The Infiniti Q60 spun after contact and continued into the Cruise AV, damaging the front bumper fascia of the Cruise AV. The driver of the Infiniti Q60 was transported by police. There were no reported injuries and both the Infiniti Q60 and the black sedan were towed from the scene.

This page is additional information reflecting the other party involved, and is in relation to the other vehicle, the Infiniti Q60 ("Vehicle 2"). The narrative for the accident details remains the same as the narrative for "Vehicle 2" page. On the following page, the check marks refer to Vehicle 2 (Infiniti Q60) and Vehicle 3 (Sedan).

address/location of accident: Leavenworth Street at Golden Gate Avenue
accident decription: On July 21, 2023 at 9:51 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on Leavenworth Street at Golden Gate Avenue.  The collision occurred while the Waymo AV was stopped in the leftmost lane of a two-lane, one-way road at the intersection of Leavenworth Street at Golden Gate Avenue. The Waymo AV was stopped before the intersection, yielding to blocking cross-traffic when the light turned yellow. At that point, a passenger car that had been stopped behind the Waymo AV passed the Waymo AV on the left and proceeded into the intersection. While passing the Waymo AV, the passenger car’s rear passenger side door made contact with the driver side rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The passenger car did not stop but appears to have sustained damage.

On July 22, 2023 at 11:11 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger vehicle on 13th Street east of Folsom Street.The Waymo AV was facing east while stopped just left of the right turn lane on 13th Street, with stopped traffic to the right. After waiting to merge, the Waymo AV reversed slightly to reroute and while doing so, a sensor on the right front of the Waymo AV made contact with the left rear side of a vehicle in the right turn lane. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The other vehicle sustained damage.

On Monday, July 24th, a Nuro Prius operating in manual mode was stopped at a red light at the intersection of Monecito and Shoreline. The light turned green and the Nuro Prius was waiting for traffic ahead to proceed, when a vehicle approaching the intersection failed to slow down and rear-ended the Nuro Prius. No injuries were reported. The drivers exchanged insurance information. The Nuro Prius had minor damage to its rear bumper and lidar.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("Cruise AV"), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling northbound on Van Ness Avenue between California Street and Sacramento Street. As the Cruise AV was passing through the intersection with Sacramento Street on a green light, a bag lying on the roadway blew in front of the Cruise AV. The Cruise AV braked for the object, and a white pickup truck traveling behind the Cruise AV rear-ended the Cruise AV, damaging the rear right bumper, rear right quarter panel, and rear windshield. The driver of the white pickup truck left the scene without exchanging information. There were no reported injuries and the Cruise AV was towed.

On July 29, 2023 at 2:57 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in Santa Monica, California was in a collision involving a cyclist on Colorado Avenue near Ocean Avenue.The Waymo AV was stopped in traffic on southwestbound Colorado Avenue when a cyclist that had been traveling behind the Waymo AV passed the Waymo AV on the right. As the cyclist passed the Waymo AV, the cyclist made contact with the front passenger side sensor of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo AV sustained damage and the cyclist did not stop, leaving the scene without exchanging information.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle (“AV”), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling northbound on Mission Street between Virginia Avenue and 29th Street. As the AV was yielding to oncoming traffic in preparation to make a left turn onto westbound 29th Street on a green light, a dark-colored BMW Sedan traveling behind the AV failed to stop and rear-ended the AV, damaging the rear passenger side bumper fascia and rear passenger side wheel molding of the AV. The driver of the dark-colored BMW Sedan left the scene without exchanging information. There were no reported injuries.

On August 2, 2023 at 10:09 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving an SUV on Bush Street at Polk Street.The Waymo AV was stopped at a red light on eastbound Bush Street at Polk Street. Shortly after the traffic light turned green and the Waymo AV began to proceed forward, the Waymo AV slowed to a stop. The SUV that was traveling closely behind the Waymo AV made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. Both vehicles sustained damage, and the trailing SUV left the scene without exchanging information. A passenger in the Waymo AV reported injuries.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle (“AV”), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling northbound on Pennsylvania Avenue between 23rd Street and 25th Street when the AV approached a double-parked semi-trailer truck in the AV’s lane of travel. The AV began to maneuver around and to the left of the semi-trailer truck and came to a stop for a stop sign at the intersection with 23rd Street. At the same time, the semi-trailer truck proceeded forward and, shortly thereafter, made contact with the AV. This caused damage to the front passenger side bumper fascia of the AV. The parties exchanged information and there were no reported injuries.

address/location of accident: North Curson Avenue at Waring Avenue
accident decription: On August 11, 2023 at 7:38 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in Los Angeles, California was in a collision involving a stationary object on North Curson Avenue at Waring Avenue.The Waymo AV was pulling over to the right side of the road, when the test driver transitioned to manual mode and made contact with a recycling bin on the right side of the street. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was not engaged and a test driver was operating the Waymo AV in manual mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage.

On August 13, 2023 at 9:01 PM a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on Howard Street at Fourth Street.The Waymo AV was traveling southwestbound on Howard Street in the second lane from the left as it was approaching Fourth Street. As the Waymo AV was proceeding straight through the intersection, the passenger car in the right adjacent lane made a left turn from a straight-only lane onto southeastbound Fourth Street. The rear of the passenger car made contact with the front of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was not engaged and a test driver was operating the Waymo AV in manual mode. Both the Waymo AV and the passenger car sustained damage.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle (“AV”), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling southbound on Albion Street between 16th Street and Camp Street. At the same time, a Ford pickup truck was traveling northbound on Albion Street partially in the AV’s lane of travel. The AV stopped due to limited space to proceed forward due to the encroaching Ford pickup truck, and, shortly thereafter, the Ford pickup truck made contact with the AV, damaging the AV’s rear driver side bumper fascia, rear driver side quarter panel and rear driver side wheel molding. The driver of the Ford pickup truck left the scene without exchanging information. There were no reported injuries.

A registered Ghost AV Test vehicle was hit by crash debris while traveling on I-680 N. The Ghost vehicle neither hit nor was hit by another vehicle. The Ghost car was traveling in AV mode with a registered AV Test Driver behind the wheel and an additional Safety Co-Driver in the passenger seat. Traffic slowed quickly due to a crash ahead of the Ghost car. Consistent with their training, the Ghost driver took control by braking and disengaging the autonomous system. The Ghost car stopped without impacting the preceding car. A Mercedes car immediately following the Ghost car also came to a stop without impacting the Ghost car. Ghost's understanding based on communications at the scene is that a Grand Cherokee traveling behind the Mercedes tried to swerve to avoid impacting the Mercedes but clipped the Mercedes and rolled over. To Ghost's knowledge, nobody in the Grand Cherokee was injured. The Ghost drivers heard a noise and then found that the rear bumper of the Ghost car had been damaged, which Ghost believes resulted from crash debris. The Ghost drivers drove the Ghost car back to the garage in conventional mode.

A Zoox vehicle in manual mode was slowing (with brake lights illuminated) in bumper-to-bumper traffic on westbound Sagamore St.approaching Orizaba St. when it was struck from behind by a following vehicle (vehicle 2). There was minor damage apparent to the hoodof the striking vehicle and no damage to the Zoox vehicle. There were no injuries and police were not called.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("AV"), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was at a complete stop in response to a stop sign on eastbound 17th Street at the intersection with Vermont Street. As the AV began to proceed straight, a gray Honda Odyssey traveling westbound on 17th Street on the opposite side of the intersection from the AV entered the intersection and veered into the AV’s lane of travel. The AV stopped in response as the Honda Odyssey continued traveling in the AV’s lane of travel through the intersection and, shortly thereafter, the Honda Odyssey made contact with the AV, damaging the front and rear driver side doors, front driver side radar assembly and rear driver side tire of the AV. The parties exchanged information. There were no reported injuries and the AV was towed from the scene.

On August 17, 2023 at 1:05 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving an SUV on Bayshore Boulevard near Jerrold Avenue. The Waymo AV was traveling northbound on Bayshore Boulevard. As the SUV was passing the Waymo AV to the left, it initiated a right lane change. The front of the SUV made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. Both vehicles sustained damage, and the SUV left the scene without exchanging information.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle (“AV”), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was at a complete stop in response to a red light on eastbound 26th Street at the intersection with Mission Street. As the AV was proceeding after the light turned green, a Dodge Charger traveling southbound on Mission Street failed to stop for the red light, entered the intersection, and made contact with the AV, damaging the front and rear driver side and rear bumper fascia of the AV. Police and Emergency Medical Services (EMS) were called to the scene. The AV was towed from the scene. The passenger of the Dodge Charger was assessed by medical personnel at the scene and was not transported by EMS.

Manufacturers Name: Mercedes-Benz Research & Development North America, Inc.
business name: Mercedes-Benz Research & Development North America, Inc.
accident decription: The driver was manually driving the Mercedes-Benz  vehicle on the interchange from the 105W to 405S when the vehicle in front of him came to an abrupt stop due to slowed traffic on the freeway.  The driver manually brought the Mercedes-Benz vehicle to a stop in his lane.  The vehicle behind him did not come to a stop in time and rear ended the Mercedes-Benz.  There was no injury or property damage. The Mercedes-Benz was able to drive away from the accident.  Damange was sustained to the rear bumper of the Mercedes Benz and the front bumper of the following vehicle. At no point during the incident was the vehicle operating in autonomous mode.

On August 19, 2023 at 4:45 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on 13th Street at Mission Street.The Waymo AV entered the slip lane which connects westbound 13th Street to northbound Mission Street and came to a stop to yield to cross-traffic on Mission Street. As the Waymo AV was stopped, the front of the passenger car which was traveling behind the Waymo AV made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo AV sustained damage.

address/location of accident: Martin Luther King Jr. Drive at Crossover Drive
accident decription: On August 20, 2023 at 5:49 PM PT the mirror of a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, CA was struck by a cyclist on Martin Luther King Jr. Drive at Crossover Drive.The Waymo AV was stopped in traffic on eastbound Martin Luther King Jr. Drive at the intersection with Crossover Drive, when a cyclist that had been traveling behind the Waymo AV passed the Waymo AV on the left. As the cyclist passed the Waymo AV, the cyclist made contact with the driver side mirror of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo AV sustained damage and the cyclist did not stop, leaving the scene without exchanging information.

address/location of accident: 9th St at Seven Seas Ave, Treasure Island
accident decription: At approximately 5:54 p.m. PST on Wednesday, August 23, 2023, at the intersection of Seven Seas Ave and 9th Street on Treasure Island in the city of San Francisco, a Beep-operated autonomous shuttle was proceeding in autonomous mode straight E/B after stopping at a 3-way stop intersection when a vehicle making a left turn heading N/B proceeded out of turn resulting in a collision within the intersection. There were no passengers on board and no injuries reported. Both vehicle sustained minor damage and police did not respond to the scene.  There were no other witness statements received.

On August 23, 2023 at 9:54 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a heavy truck on Mason Street at Vandewater Street.The Waymo AV was traveling northbound on Mason Street when it approached a heavy truck and trailer that was stopped in the adjacent lane on the left side of the street. As the Waymo began to slowly pass the truck, the truck initiated a reversing turn maneuver into a loading bay on the left side of Mason Street. The Waymo AV then came to a stop, and as the Waymo AV was initiating its own reversing maneuver to clear the path for the truck, the right side of the trailer made contact with the front driver’s side corner of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage.

On August 24, 2023 at 4:39 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in Santa Monica, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on Michigan Avenue at Euclid Street. The Waymo AV was traversing a roundabout at the intersection of Michigan Avenue at Euclid Street when it slowed to a stop for other vehicles approaching and in the roundabout. The front of the passenger car that was in the roundabout behind the Waymo AV made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. Both vehicles sustained damage.

address/location of accident: East 8th Street and South Main Street
accident decription: On September 3, 2023 at 12:25 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in Los Angeles, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on East 8th Street and South Main Street. The Waymo AV was parked on the right side of East 8th Street when a passenger car approached from the left and made contact with the left side mirror of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was not engaged and a test driver was operating the Waymo AV in manual mode. Both vehicles sustained damage.

An Apollo autonomous vehicle (“AV”) was traveling westbound on Rivera Street in San Francisco in autonomous mode and stopped for a double-parked vehicle near 31st Avenue. An Apollo safety operator disengaged the AV from autonomous mode into conventional mode with use of the steering wheel. Then the AV side-swiped the double-parked vehicle while in conventional mode. There were no injuries and emergency services were not needed. Both the AV and the second vehicle sustained minor damage.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("AV"), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was at a complete stop in response to a red light on eastbound Bush Street in the second leftmost lane at the intersection with Sansome Street. As the AV attempted to maneuver into the left turn lane, the AV slowed to a complete stop. A delivery truck traveling behind and to the left of the AV proceeded forward and attempted to drive past the AV on the left. Shortly thereafter, the delivery truck made contact with the AV, damaging the AV’s front driver side bumper fascia and front driver side wheel opening molding. The driver of the delivery truck left the scene without exchanging information. There were no reported injuries.

On September 11, 2023 at 8:34 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving an SUV on Sansome Street near Vallejo Street. While the Waymo AV was pulled over in the right lane on northbound Sansome Street, an SUV that was passing the parked Waymo AV made contact with the rear driver’s side of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was not engaged and a test driver was operating the Waymo AV in manual mode. Both vehicles sustained damage.

A Zoox vehicle in autonomy was slowing to a gradual stop on eastbound Folsom St. for a red light at 7th St. when it was rear-ended by vehicle 2 at approximately 10 mph. There was minor damage, no reported injuries, and police were not called.

On September 15, 2023, a Pony.ai autonomous vehicle (AV) collided with road debris while operating in supervised autonomous ("Drivered") mode northbound on the 880 freeway, preparing to enter the Dixon Landing exit.Immediately prior to the incident, the safety driver noticed a flat item was in the center part of the lane. The driver disengaged from autonomous mode and attempted to dodge the debris. However, the debris struck the rear bumper slightly damaging it.Following the collision, the safety operator promptly drove the AV to Pony.ai's Fremont office. There were no injuries reported, and the police were not called.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("AV"), operating in manual mode, was traveling northbound on 25th Avenue between California Street and Clement Street. The AV operator improperly engaged from manual into autonomous mode while the AV was in motion, temporarily causing the AV to steer to the right. The AV operator then disengaged from autonomous mode into manual mode, and shortly thereafter, the AV made contact with an unoccupied and parked red Chrysler Voyager. This caused damage to the AV’s front passenger side bumper fascia. The AV operator left contact information for the other party and there were no reported injuries.

On September 26th, a test vehicle operating with the automated driving system engaged was traveling Westbound on Interstate 80 in Emeryville, CA, when it slowed and came to a complete stop in response to traffic. Approximately three seconds later, and while traffic remained stopped ahead, a white Chevrolet Silverado made contact from the rear. No injuries were reported and law enforcement was not called to the scene. Both vehicles sustained damage.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle (“AV”), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling northbound on 2nd Street between Stillman Street and Bryant Street. As the AV was approaching the intersection with Stillman Street, a blue Model 3 Tesla exited out of a parking garage into the AV’s lane of travel. The AV braked and, shortly thereafter, the AV made contact with the Model 3 Tesla, damaging the AV’s front bumper fascia and front passenger side wheel opening molding. The driver of the Model 3 Tesla left the scene without exchanging information. There were no reported injuries. The driver of the Model 3 Tesla later reported damages.

address/location of accident: On Embarcadero St left turning lane to Howard St
accident decription: At 1:54pm, a WeRide vehicle (Car 1) was stopped on Embarcadero St left turning lane to Howard St. As our vehicle (Car 1) was stopped for red traffic light, the toyota suv (Car 2) approaching from behind collided with our vehicle (Car 1). Both parties pulled over both involved vehicles and cooperated to exchange information. The damage sustained to the WeRide vehicle (Car 1) and toyota suv (Car 2) are minor.

On September 29th, a test vehicle operating with the automated driving system engaged was traveling Southbound on Highway 101 in San Jose when a nearby white Jeep Cherokee ran over a piece of lumber, which was projected onto the test vehicle.  No injuries were reported and law enforcement was not called to the scene.  The test vehicle sustained minor damage.

On September 20th, 2023 at 9:00 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on US-101 exit ramp 429B at the intersection with Bayshore Boulevard.The Waymo AV was proceeding south on exit ramp 429B in the leftmost lane and entered the slip lane to proceed north on Bayshore Boulevard. As the Waymo AV came to a stop for a red light at the intersection with Bayshore Boulevard, the front of the passenger car which was following behind the Waymo AV made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. The Waymo AV sustained damage. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("AV"), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was stopped for a passenger pick-up in the AV’s lane of travel on northbound Scott Street between Oak Street and Page Street. After picking up the passenger while the AV remained stopped, a white Mercedes-Benz Metris reversed out of a driveway and made contact with the AV, damaging the AV’s front driver side door and front driver side auxiliary mirror. The parties exchanged information and there were no reported injuries.

A Zoox vehicle was being driven in manual mode eastbound on Jackson street between Montgomery and Sansome Streets when contact was made with the left side mirror of a parked car. There was minor damage to the Zoox vehicle's sensor housing and passenger side mirror. There were no injuries and police were not called.

On October 13th, a test vehicle operating with the automated driving system engaged was traveling Northbound on Interstate 880 in San Jose. The safety driver disengaged just prior to running over a piece of sheet metal in the road. No injuries were reported and law enforcement was not called to the scene. The vehicle sustained minor damage.

An Apollo autonomous vehicle (“AV”) was traveling westbound on Ortega Street in San Francisco in conventional mode with a safety operator driving. At the intersection with 46th Ave.,  the right front of the AV made contact with the curb and the AV traveled onto the curb. The safety operator was able to drive off the curb and back onto the street.  No other vehicles or property were involved. There were no injuries and the police were not called. The AV sustained minor damage to right wheel fender shield and the right lower bumper.

On October 17, 2023 at 9:24 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a cyclist on Market Street at Gough Street. The Waymo AV was in autonomous mode on eastbound Market Street preparing to make a right turn onto southbound Gough Street and had stopped to yield, first for pedestrians to cross Gough Street and then for a cyclist approaching from behind traveling eastbound on the sidewalk of Market Street. As the pedestrians finished crossing Gough Street but before the cyclist had reached Gough Street, the Waymo AV test driver took manual control of the Waymo AV and began to accelerate and perform the right turn onto Gough Street. After the Waymo AV entered the crosswalk, the cyclist entered the crosswalk and made contact with the passenger’s rear quarter panel of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was not engaged and a test driver was operating the Waymo AV in manual mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage.

On October 23rd, a test vehicle operating in manual driving mode was stopped at a red light in the righthand lane of Lawrence Expressway at the intersection with Kifer Road in Santa Clara.  A Lexus RX300 attempted to pass through traffic in the adjacent bike lane, and made contact with the test vehicle’s side mirror. No injuries were reported and law enforcement was not called to the scene. The test vehicle sustained minor damage.
